LONDON. Arsenal have had a bid in excess of 30 million turned down for Monaco winger Thomas Lemar and are now considering whether to formalise their interest in Leicester City s Riyad Mahrez. Ars ne Wenger s transfer priorities have been the French trio of Kylian Mbapp , Alexandre Lacazette and Lemar, with Arsenal hoping to sign two new forwards ahead of Alexis S nchez s likely departure.Arsenal are now preparing a new raid on Monaco for star man Lemar.Lemar is wanted by the Gunners this summer.But so far the English Premier League soccer giants haven t made any headway with a deal.The Times reported yesterday that an opening 31m offer for the French midfielder has been knocked back by Monaco.And they add a renewed bid of closer to 35m is now being prepeared. The Daily Star.